Hi! I'll be reviewing Sunshine Turquoise from @ohmykitty4u .These lenses are really vibrant yet almost natural-looking. They sell it for $19.90 only!!. I am actually waiting for the wig Im using for this cosplay but since it's taking so long, here are my thoughts on the lenses: 
Ratings: 
Color and Design: (5/5) ★★★★★
I was really in need of lenses that would look visible even from a afar that aren't animation lenses with creepy designs. What intrigued me of these lenses are the gold that lines in the middle of it that blends with your real eye color. The lenses contain the right amount of pigment that makes it stand out but not look distracting.

Comfort: (5/5) ★★★★★
These lenses are super comfortable and do not irritate my eyes. I might be used to wearing and inserting lenses but there are lenses that still sting the first time I put them on. Since these come with prescription, I can really see better with them without feeling discomfort. They even feel natural and it was as if I was not wearing lenses in the first place!

Enlargement: (5/5) ★★★★★ These lenses have a diameter of 15mm and are perfect for making your eyes look cute, large and doll-like. They make your eyes pop up more without making people weirded out with it.

Visibility of Effect: (5/5) ★★★★★ When I forst tried them, it was after sunset and it was really dark. I could still see the lenses and I was even sitting quite far from the mirror. Unlike animation lenses that look intimidating, these look like a foreigner's eye that are super pigmented. I really recommend getting these since they can be used in cosplay and in everyday life. 
Overall: (5/5) ★★★★★
These are one of the best lenses to ever exist! They are very pigmented, clear, have a great diameter and are very eye-catching. It isn't intimidating or weird to look at and it can pass for natural lenses. They are also very affordable and @ohmykitty4u provides great service. #ohmykitty4u #contacts #Cosplay #circlelenses #eyes #makeup
